properties.description: Whether to include deleted events (with status equals "cancelled") in the result. Cancelled instances of recurring events (but not the underlying recurring event) will still be included if showDeleted and singleEvents are both False. If showDeleted and singleEvents are both True, only single instances of deleted events (but not the underlying recurring events) are returned.
properties.name: showDeleted
properties.label: Show deleted

properties.description: Whether to include hidden invitations in the result.
properties.name: showHiddenInvitations
properties.label: Show hidden invitations

properties.name: singleEvents
properties.label: Single events

properties.description: Upper bound (exclusive) for an event's start time to filter by. The default is not to filter by start time. Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMin is set, timeMax must be greater than timeMin.
properties.name: timeMax
properties.label: Time max

properties.description: Lower bound (exclusive) for an event's end time to filter by. Optional. The default is not to filter by end time. Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMax is set, timeMin must be smaller than timeMax.
properties.name: timeMin
properties.label: Time min

properties.description: Time zone used in the response.
properties.name: timeZone
properties.label: Time zone

properties.description: Lower bound for an event's last modification time (as a RFC3339 timestamp) to filter by. When specified, entries deleted since this time will always be included regardless of showDeleted.
properties.name: updatedMin
properties.label: Update min
